Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 21:42:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 11/14] web-app: webimap login toggle + madmail welcome-screen
 entry

Frontend surface for the madmail WebIMAP transport (HTTP mail access, no
ws-tcp bridge). madmail-only, hardcoded English per the patch-stack
convention.

- DefaultCredentials.ts: seed `webimap: null` so LoginForm's key-guard
  accepts the field. The published @deltachat/jsonrpc-client 2.53.0
  EnteredLoginParam lacks it (the regenerated local bindings add it), so
  Credentials is widened locally to keep tsc green.
- LoginForm.tsx: advanced-collapse Switch after certificateChecks,
  mirroring the enforce_e2ee row, toggling credentials.webimap.
- UseWebimapServerDialog.tsx (new): instance-address input feeding the
  stock instant-onboarding flow via `webimapaccount:<host>` +
  checkQr/startInstantOnboardingFlow; links to the madmail repo + TDD doc.
- OnboardingScreen.tsx: third welcome-screen button opening the dialog.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
(cherry picked from commit e93b78f76c5485cf9c70a238bc60d3e2577f6aca)
